{"session_id":"svc-1778366476935377217","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-09T22:41:18.956287133Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-c113a116-20260509T224106-5a54888f","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260509T224106-5a54888f/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260509T224106-5a54888f/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260509T224106-5a54888f/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260509T224106-5a54888f/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260509T224106-5a54888f/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-c113a116\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ebead/store: unify Ready definition - drop redundant Status==Open filter\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  Two places answer \u0026#34;is this bead ready?\u0026#34; and they disagree. The lifecycle\u0026#xA;  module (lifecycle.go) classifies a bead\u0026#39;s queue bucket from facts; the\u0026#xA;  store.go Ready() helper then re-filters by raw status, producing a different\u0026#xA;  answer than the lifecycle classifier when an in_progress bead has a stale\u0026#xA;  claim.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/lifecycle.go:155-208 EvaluateLifecycleQueue routes\u0026#xA;    StatusInProgress at line 190-194 through evaluateOpenLifecycleQueue when\u0026#xA;    !ClaimFresh, which can produce LifecycleBucketReady at line 232.\u0026#xA;  - cli/internal/bead/store.go:1754-1766 readyFiltered then iterates the\u0026#xA;    classifier output and applies a second filter at line 1763:\u0026#xA;        if entry.Status == StatusOpen { ready = append(...) }\u0026#xA;    This filter is gated by !executionOnly, so external readers\u0026#xA;    (ddx bead ready non-executionOnly path) see a different result than\u0026#xA;    queue-execution callers (executionOnly path).\u0026#xA;  - Net effect: a stale-claimed in_progress bead with deps satisfied is\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;ready\u0026#34; per EvaluateLifecycleQueue, \u0026#34;not ready\u0026#34; per store.Ready() in\u0026#xA;    operator-facing mode, and \u0026#34;ready\u0026#34; per store.Ready() in execution mode.\u0026#xA;    Three answers; one question.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - Decide the canonical answer: per TD-031 §6, claim metadata is not status,\u0026#xA;    and a stale-claimed in_progress bead is recoverable through the heartbeat\u0026#xA;    TTL mechanism. The lifecycle module\u0026#39;s classifier already encodes this.\u0026#xA;    Therefore the second filter at store.go:1763 is redundant and incorrect.\u0026#xA;  - Edit cli/internal/bead/store.go:1754-1766: remove the\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;if entry.Status == StatusOpen\u0026#34; branch; both executionOnly and\u0026#xA;    operator-facing paths consume LifecycleBucketReady directly.\u0026#xA;  - Add regression test TestReady_StaleClaimedInProgressIsReady in\u0026#xA;    cli/internal/bead/store_test.go (or extend an existing nearby test) that:\u0026#xA;      a. Creates a bead, claims it (open -\u0026gt; in_progress).\u0026#xA;      b. Manually expires the heartbeat (set claimed-at + heartbeat TTL).\u0026#xA;      c. Asserts Ready() returns the bead in operator-facing mode (not just\u0026#xA;         the executionOnly path).\u0026#xA;  - Verify no other call sites of readyFiltered or Ready depend on the\u0026#xA;    removed filter; grep for s.Ready, store.Ready, .Ready( across cli/.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Changing EvaluateLifecycleQueue or the lifecycle bucket enumeration.\u0026#xA;  - Adding new claim-recovery semantics.\u0026#xA;  - Migrating callers between executionOnly and non-executionOnly paths.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;  - ddx-ca1c66ee (epic parent).\u0026#xA;  - No deps on B1/B2; can run in parallel with the TD-031 amendment.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/internal/bead/store.go readyFiltered no longer applies a Status==StatusOpen filter; both executionOnly and operator-facing paths return entries whose Decision.Bucket==LifecycleBucketReady.\u0026#xA;2. TestReady_StaleClaimedInProgressIsReady in cli/internal/bead/store_test.go asserts a stale-claimed in_progress bead with satisfied deps appears in Ready() output.\u0026#xA;3. No other test in cli/internal/bead/... regresses (existing Ready/Blocked/queue tests stay green).\u0026#xA;4. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/bead/... ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... green.\u0026#xA;5. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:6, area:bead, area:lifecycle, kind:fix, spec:TD-031\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-ca1c66ee\" spec-id=\"TD-031\" base-rev=\"2fd0beed9caf1317259e921a8fcf0424ed68bd51\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260509T224106-5a54888f\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"TD-031\" path=\"docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md\"\u003eTechnical Design: Bead State Machine and Naming-Role Decisions\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260509T224106-5a54888f","base_rev":"2fd0beed9caf1317259e921a8fcf0424ed68bd51","bead_id":"ddx-c113a116","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260509T224106-5a54888f","correlation_id":"ddx-c113a116:20260509T224106-5a54888f","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260509T224106-5a54888f/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"80f73fd39d0bbbb325f17af1a04e80e1aa2ef8c8a707acaf9685395018fc1a6a","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-9937d31d","worker_id":""}}}
